{"id":2891,"date":"2012-04-16T22:21:51","date_gmt":"2012-04-16T18:21:51","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=2891"},"modified":"2025-03-14T21:31:50","modified_gmt":"2025-03-14T17:31:50","slug":"monotheism-asked-god-musa","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/16\/monotheism-asked-god-musa\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Shirk: You asked for a god like people of Moses"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Waqid al-Laythi reported: When we traveled to Hunayn with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, we passed by a tree that the idolaters called Dhat al-Anwat. They would hang their weapons upon it for blessings. I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, make a blessed tree for us, just as they have one.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Glory be to Allah! You have said just as the people of Moses said, &#8216;Make a god for us, just as they have a god&#8217; <\/strong>(7:138).<strong> By the One in whose hand is my soul, you will follow the ways of people before you.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2180<\/p>\n<p>Grade:&nbsp;<strong><em>Sahih&nbsp;<\/em><\/strong>(authentic) according to Al-Tirmidhi<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0642\u0650\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u064a\u0652\u062b\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0651\u0627 \u062e\u064e\u0631\u064e\u062c\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u062d\u064f\u0646\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u064d \u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0651 \u0628\u0650\u0634\u064e\u062c\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064d \u0644\u0650\u064